Lac Minerals Ltd reiterated it expectedsubstantially higher 1987 profit and revenues than last year'searnings of 19.1 mln dlrs on 250.2 mln dlrs of revenues.    The 1986 results include the disputed Page-Williams mine atHemlo, Ontario. A decision is imminent on Lac's appeal of a1986 Ontario court decision ordering Lac to hand over the mineto International Corona Resources Ltd &lt;ICR.TO>.    Lac chief executive Peter Allen told institutionalinvestors that the anticipated stronger performance would comefrom strong operating results and an active revenue managementprogram.       Lac said year-to-date gold production excluding thedisputed Page-Williams mine was 134,000 ounces, in line withtargeted 1987 production of 300,000 ounces. It said it expectedan average realized price of 450 U.S. dlrs an ounce infull-year 1987.    It said its outstanding forward contracts at May 29 were220,000 ounces of gold at average price of 439 U.S. dlrs anounce, including 135,000 ounces maturing in 1987 at 482 U.S.dlrs an ounce. Reuter&#3;